      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: preserve steered audio for inbound TTS",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen `tts.auto` is set to `\"inbound\"`, OpenClaw should use voice output for replies that answer inbound audio. A text-started reply run could later accept steered inbound audio while the active run was still streaming, but the final TTS decision only looked at the original text message. That meant the agent could answer the later audio while the final delivery still stayed text-only.\n\nThis is the same user-visible failure reported in #94049, but the fix avoids making steered audio a persisted session-state field.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe inbound-audio fact belongs to the current reply operation, not durable session state. This change threads `currentInboundAudio` through the active embedded-run queue options, latches it on the in-memory `ReplyOperation` only after the active run accepts the steered message, and lets final TTS resolve `inboundAudio` from either the original message or that operation-local marker.\n\nThat keeps the behavior generic across channels and avoids WhatsApp-specific delivery logic, session-entry compatibility concerns, or changes to `packages/speech-core`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers with `tts.auto: \"inbound\"` now get voice output when an active reply run is steered by a later inbound audio message and the final answer is generated from that same operation.\n\nText-only replies and non-final TTS behavior continue to use the existing original-message classification unless steered audio was actually accepted into the active operation.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/reply-run-registry.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.media-paths.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/runs.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- targeted `pnpm exec oxfmt --check` on touched files\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n",
        "branch": "fix/pr-94049-steered-inbound-audio",
